snippet.textDisplay: For anyone saying that John didn't let Bill sing his own song. These things are planned and rehearsed, it's not like John surprisingly just took over. Bill Withers clearly had a reason he could not perform the whole song, may he rest in piece. John was trying to help him out the best way he could, he was also probably nervous performing next to his idols. You can also see Bill keeping the mic very far away and not singing much, maybe he couldn't find the key or something. But come on, John did a great job, and Stevie was amazing as usual.

snippet.textDisplay:
When you learn to overcome your internally, and externally prideful self serving bias, and begin trusting others to help you with your internal, and external developmental needs, you realize people do not have to be physically present to aid you. Through the internet, online meetings, social media, phone calls, live videos, and video sharing, emails, text messaging, and other forms of communication, you can reach out for help to anyone in the Earth. This is the new form of leaning on others Bill Withers communicated in his song.
Unfortunately, not everyone has access to nor the finances to afford or the abilities to use the internet, computers, and smartphones. In the age of the coronavirus pandemic, those people are isolated from humanity, and are ineffective to trust anyone to help them at all. When life is increasingly online, leaning on online support is becoming the only means of survival. Sad as it is, I hope no one dies because of the lack of technological abilities or access.
What would you do if you wanted to be the type of person Bill Withers communicated in his song must help others trust in for their internal, and external development? You must use your internal, and external developmental strengths since birth to use technological media to aid others developmental needs across the generations, and their lifespan. Otherwise, humanity cannot, and will not survive social isolation without becoming lonely, depressed, and desperate until they slowly become insane from lack of interpersonal relations with each other. We must not allow that to happen. It is far too deadly a price to pay, and still assume we will remain a healthy populous across the globe.
